Results.ReviewText: NESCAFE Gold Black its rich, intense, aroma awakens my senses every morning...mmmm, followed by the taste of GOLD upon my tongue, rich, dark, smooth, waking my mind, body and spirits EVERY morning!  Nescafe Gold Black rich, beautiful, coffee without any bitterness that many other 'intense' coffees can suffer from.  A GOLD standard coffee that is decadent but affordable enough to drink all day every day!
Results.Title: Black is MY new GOLD!

Results.ReviewText: I have been buying this coffee for years! No other coffee comes anywhere close to this. Now it's changed and at first I was upset, it is a finer blend and leaves some deposit in the end... But the strength I always crave is still there...  The richness that fulfils me is still there... The great taste is always there. It's just  a little more sophisticated...  I can live with that!
Results.Title: Delightful full body of sophistication!

Results.ReviewText:
Bought this for a change when it first came out. I found it had a nice coffee smell when i opened the jar. When hot water is poured on the granules ot has a creamy appearance. Overall it is a more intense Gold blend flavour but without a delayed aftertaste that sometimes occurs after some coffees.
Definitely my favourite choice having been a gold blend drinker for over 35 years
Results.Title: Stronger but velvety taste

Results.ReviewText:
Usually buy expensive Colombian coffee but noticed new branding so thought i would give it a try. Take my coffee black , so always get a good idea on flavour .
Was really surprised by full bodied taste at a much more competitive price of the coffee I used to buy . Well done Nescafe...you coffee lovers out there, give Nescafe Gold Black a taste , you wont be dissappointed.
Results.Title: Great taste...

Results.ReviewText: Any coffee lover is going to prefer freshly ground roasted beans, slowly percolated to draw out a full flavour. Reality is though that we seldom have that much time on our hands during a busy day. Hence the creation of Instant Coffee. With NEscafe Gold Black - you get the utter convenience of an instant but a flavour which gets pretty darn close to a "proper" coffee taste.
Results.Title: Instant enjoyment

Results.ReviewText: As a very busy and in demand person I need a coffee in the morning which will give me the pick up and fly start to my day, Nescafe Gold Black is my number one drink with its rich and full bodied strong taste it gives me the kick start that I need to power my adrenaline to cope with whatever the day ahead will bring, as well as keeping me mentally and physically alert.
Results.Title: My go to coffee in the morning

Results.ReviewText: I have drunk Nescafe Gold for years and recently picked up another jar, or so I thought, to find it was Gold Black, when I got home. The first mug was enough to bless my mistake, the flavour is excellent and really enjoyable. I have taken Cappuchino sachets to work as I don't like the brand they provide but when my stock is finished I think it will be Gold Black.
Results.Title: Sharp Beautiful Taste

Results.ReviewText: I thought I'd give this a try, a change from my regular brand which would be hard to beat. This was absolutely delicious! A strong, but not bitter, a toasted coffee bean on the nose also got a hint of black treacle, vanilla aroma. This was exceptionally smooth, no bitter after taste that you associate with strong coffees. Delicious !! I have to buy this again!
Results.Title: Exceptionally Smooth

Results.ReviewText: I have always been a fan of Nescafe but when I discovered this range I fell in love with it. It is as strong as it is necessary to wake me up in the morning and not many can take credit for that! Full of flavour and distinctive taste. I have also used it in cakes and find that is perfect for them to get a lovely coffee aroma.  I would recommend to everyone.
Results.Title: Excellent flavour

Results.ReviewText:
As coffee lovers we thought we'd try something different to our usual brand and decided to try Nescafe Gold Black.

To say we were impressed is an understatement!

The Nescafe Gold Black, is rich, smooth and aromatic.  It smells so good that you just can't resist.

The taste is delightful, leaving you wanting more and more!

Simply divine!
Results.Title: Simply the best!

Results.ReviewText: I bought this about 3 weeks ago to try , as I'd heard good things from my friends , I usually drink Nescafe Original and never dreamed that after so many years of drinking the same wonderful coffee that I would be transformed into a totally NEW experience . It is a wonderful flavour and I can see myself drinking this coffe for years to come !!!
Results.Title: Transformed

Results.ReviewText: I am a huge fan of black Americano coffee and love to experiment with different beans. However sometimes when I am at home I need a fix of dark, smooth coffee in an instant. This new products really hits the spot for me, its dark and tasty without the bitterness when I heap up the spoon ! Thank you Nescafe for bringing the 'real' into coffee!!
Results.Title: Hits the Americano spot !!

Results.ReviewText: I have been a fan of Nescafe Gold Blend for years, so was intrigued to see this new addition. It couldn't possibly be as good, I thought. Wrong! It is in fact even better. It has all the richness, depth and aroma of the original Gold Blend, but with added body and flavour. It really is most delicious! I will most definitely keep buying it.
Results.Title: Gorgeous coffee!

Results.ReviewText: Recently changed from Gold Blend to the Black version, like my coffee with a strong full flavour whilst being smooth and not bitter as some of the coffee shop ones are, Black delivered in full, lovely full smooth flavour. Nice aroma when you open the jar for the first time, great value for money . My coffee of choice now as love the taste
Results.Title: Lovely Flavour

Results.ReviewText: I bought Nescafé Gold Black as my husband was complaining that all the coffees we’ve had recently are very tasteless and this one looked like a good strong option. As it turned out, I made a great choice as Gold Black has a lovely ‘proper’ coffee taste that my husband loves, as do I. It is now our go-to coffee that we enjoy every day.
Results.Title: A ‘Proper’ Coffee Taste!

Results.ReviewText: We have been drinking Alta Rica for as long as I can remember as it has that strong taste but none of the bitterness you get from cheaper roasts. Gave this a try and although it is better than the cheaper coffees it still hasn't the finesse that Alta Rica has. We have converted most of our friends to Alta Rica.
Results.Title: Not bad but not as good as Alta Rica

Results.ReviewText: This Nescafé is so rich and full-flavoured, yet not overpowering.  I really appreciate the first coffee and this coffee's a brilliant way to start any day.  However, Nescafé Gold Black's full body is also especially good made with hot milk, and is very satisfying with supper.  Great all round, I'm a big fan!
Results.Title: Rich, great coffee!

Results.ReviewText: I always drank carte noir, but one day I decided to try nescafe gold black, and for me nescafe has a smooth flavour and still you get that boost of caffeine, the different flavours is exceptional and I love drinking the decaff as well, it's so affordable and delicious to drink, would highly recommend it
Results.Title: Coffee

Results.ReviewText: I bought this 2 weeks ago, and its the best instant coffee I have ever tasted. I like really strong coffee and I usually use 3 teaspoons per cup, but with this I don't need to, it's really rich and smooth and intensely flavoured. The days I can't get to Starbucks I drink this and its fast taking over!
Results.Title: Super smooth and intense

Results.ReviewText:
I always love tasting new coffee's and when I tried this, I was really happy as the flavour was just right full of body yet not bitter, this is now my new coffee, so well done Nescaf'e.
Great cooffee I would recommend this coffee to anyone that loves a full rounded coffee you won't be dissapointed.
Results.Title: My New Coffee

Results.UserLocation: Walsall, Birmingham, West Midlands, United Kingdom
Results.ReviewText: I was intrigued  by this coffee, hence bought a bottle and was truly impressed. It has a refreshing aroma, unique smooth taste like a real coffee. Good as black coffee or with cream. Liked by my family and friends, highly recommended. (sorry, don't own smart phone, hence could not upload any photo)
Results.Title: Great Coffee

Results.ReviewText: I'd really been a fan of the intense taste of Nescafe Alta, so it was great to compare the new Nescafe Gold Black. It was all I expected, rich, dark and full of deep coffee flavour. It's really suited to that first, open-your-eyes cup in the morning or served after a great meal. Go grab this Gold.
Results.Title: Bold, Black and Beautiful Tasting

Results.ReviewText:
OMG!!! this coffee was like an explosionof tastes!! It was smooth and strong. You could taste the different flavours and it definitely hit the spot!!!
Its one of the best coffees I have had of the shelve in a very long time!! So well done to whoever genius put this together! You've won me over :)
Results.Title: Gold black and dark!!

Results.ReviewText: Not a big instant coffee fan.Got this for friends popping round and had it left over so thought give it a try. To my surprise I really like it. Tastes like actual coffee not that fake instant flavour. Definitely could be a morning pick me up at work. Rich taste with no bitterness. Very quaffable.
Results.Title: Better than usual instant coffee

Results.ReviewText: Been drinking Nescafe Gold Black for years now and have always loved it to the extent my palette won't accept any other instants. When it changed I was worried that i may not like this change but i need not have. It's still the smooth strong taste i'm used to and is still my only go to instant.
Results.Title: The best got better

Results.ReviewText: I tried this on an introductory offer a few weeks ago and am hooked.  All the flavour of freshly brewed coffee with the convenience of instant.  I have since re-stocked and visitors think I have poured this from a caffetiere.  Good result all round.  Love the styish look of the packaging too.
Results.Title: Exceptional!

Results.ReviewText: Drunk Gold Blend since my childhood and recently switched to Gold Blend Black, as it was on offer and it was a wise decision. A much more intense coffee taste without the bitterness you can sometimes get or having to ask for an extra shot. If you like strong coffee, then i'd try this one out
Results.Title: A change for the better

Results.ReviewText: The roast characteristics of this coffee really stand out to me. The darker roast develops a more toffee like sweetness and a rich cocoa flavour is rounded off by the creamy mouthfeel, reminding me of chocolate. The acidity is very mild and there is a pleasant bitterness in the aftertaste.”
Results.Title: The pleasure of chocolate.

Results.ReviewText: I am still waiting for someone to bring out an instance coffee that tastes as good and strong as a percolated coffee.  I love a good tasting strong flavour to let me know I am drinking coffee and have still yet to find the exact replica.  Enjoyable however, just missing a little something.
Results.Title: GOOD BUT NOT EXCELLENT!

Results.ReviewText: Well you want a review, What can I say it is a lovely coffee if you like strong coffee this is the one for you. I only drink strong black coffee and to be honest this is the only one that I drink. If you like ground coffee this is the one for you all the flavour without the mess.
Results.Title: Ground coffee without the mess
